3.Given an array arr[] consisting of n integers, the task is to find all the array elements which occurs more than floor(n/3) times.
platform : GeeksForGeeks 
SOURCECODE : class Solution {
    public ArrayList<Integer> findMajority(int[] arr) {
        // Code here
        Arrays.sort(arr);
        ArrayList<Integer> list=new ArrayList<>();
        int n=arr.length;
        int count=1;
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            if(arr[i]==arr[i-1]){
                count++;
            }
            else{
                if(count>n/3){
                    list.add(arr[i-1]);
                }
                count=1;
            }
        }
        if(count>n/3){
            list.add(arr[n-1]);
        }
        return list;
    }
}
Link : https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/majority-vote/1
4.The cost of stock on each day is given in an array price[]. Each day you may decide to either buy or sell the stock i at price[i], you can even buy and sell the stock on the same day. Find the maximum profit that you can get.
platform : GeeksForGeeks 
SOURCECODE : class Solution {
    public int maxProfit(int prices[]) {
         int n=prices.length;int profit=0;
         for(int i=1;i<=n-1;i++){
             if(prices[i]>prices[i-1]){
                 profit+=prices[i]-prices[i-1];
             }
         }
    return profit;}
}
